-- TriGranit Gets 119 Million-Euro Loan for New Polish Project
-- B y   L o u i s e   M e e s o n
-- 2012-01-17T17:40:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/trigranit-gets-119-million-euro-loan-for-new-polish-project.html
TriGranit Development Corp., a
Hungarian real-estate developer, signed a 119 million-euro ($152
million) loan.  The facility will finance the company’s largest development
project in  Poland  - a 250 million-euro railway and bus station
and shopping center in Poznan, according to a  statement  on
TriGranit’s website.  Bank Zachodni WBK SA, Raiffeisen Bank Polska SA, Nordea
Bank Polska SA, BRE Bank SA and HYPO NOE Gruppe Bank AG were
involved in the deal, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Meeson in  London  on 
 lmeeson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 Fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 